465
00:27:19,940 --> 00:27:20,540
Professor.

466
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:22,820
Why don't we give out queue numbers?

467
00:27:22,980 --> 00:27:24,620
Then, we can treat the patients
in sequence.

468
00:27:24,700 --> 00:27:25,460
What do you think?

469
00:27:28,340 --> 00:27:29,740
That's a good idea.

470
00:27:30,660 --> 00:27:31,300
Mr. An.

471
00:27:31,460 --> 00:27:33,420
Can you please do a headcount later?

472
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:34,740
Prepare the queue numbers

473
00:27:34,780 --> 00:27:36,140
and distribute them to the villagers.

474
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:36,780
Sure.

475
00:27:37,540 --> 00:27:39,260
Let's work in groups of two.

476
00:27:39,380 --> 00:27:40,260
- Of course.
- Sure.

477
00:27:40,420 --> 00:27:41,820
Sen and I will team up.

478
00:27:42,260 --> 00:27:42,620
Sen.

479
00:27:42,660 --> 00:27:43,540
Let's go.

480
00:27:47,940 --> 00:27:49,420
The potato pancake is really delicious.

481
00:27:49,540 --> 00:27:50,620
It contains a lot of
plant-based ingredients.

482
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:51,620
Give it a taste.

483
00:27:55,420 --> 00:27:58,020
Don't you enjoy having all the nice food
back in Shanghai?

484
00:27:58,260 --> 00:28:00,540
You are putting a lot of effort
into winning Xizhou's heart.

485
00:28:02,140 --> 00:28:03,740
I'll bring this to Xizhou.

486
00:28:05,940 --> 00:28:07,540
